SUPERVISOR FIX + DIVERGENCE (2026-06-15 audit fire): gm-plugkit/supervisor.js spawnWatcher child.on('exit') labeled EVERY non-version-change respawn 'unplanned-restart-after-exit', so a clean/planned exit (reason 'process-exit', exit_code 0, isPlanned true) misreads as a crash in the next watcher's boot_reason - it false-alarmed this audit. FIX (gm-plugkit/supervisor.js:267): respawnReason now = version-change -> 'planned-restart-version-change'; isPlanned -> `planned-restart-after-${reason||'clean-exit'}`; else 'unplanned-restart-after-exit'. isPlanned/reason/cleanExit in scope; node --check passes. Ships via publish.yml (push to non-ignored path auto-bumps gm.json+package.json PATCH, republishes gm-plugkit). NOTICING/CANDIDATE: TWO live divergent supervisor implementations - bin/plugkit-supervisor.js (installed by lib/skill-bootstrap.js ensureSupervisorInstalled, emits generic supervisor.watcher-exited with respawn_reason exit-<code>) vs gm-plugkit/supervisor.js (used by `bun x gm-plugkit spool`, emits granular watcher-exited-clean/idle/for-update/lock-rejected/unexpectedly). Different event schemas by boot path = observability blind spot for gmsniff/audit-loop supervisor-health scan + a predictability gap; converging them to one implementation/schema is a dedicated-fire refactor (risky core infra, needs its own PRD), not a rushed change. The 11:36 restart that triggered this was benign (clean planned restart, supervisor resilience + single-instance refuse-duplicate working).